Subject: Social Periphery Interest Fabric

Description: Future specification for mapping interest-node relationships across local social networks through consented periphery overlap and trust-lensed recommendations.

@ [source] C:\Project\Pinky\.sop\platform\source_documents\2026-06-25_social_periphery_interest_fabric\Dictated_Social_Periphery_Interest_Fabric_Source.sop
@ [source] C:\Project\Pinky\.sop\platform\SOPSwarmFabric.sop
@ [source] C:\Project\Pinky\.sop\platform\SemanticCorrelationGraph.sop
@ [source] C:\Project\Pinky\.sop\platform\SemanticHashIndex.sop
@ [source] C:\Project\Pinky\.sop\platform\LocalIdentityConsumption.sop
@ [source] C:\Project\Pinky\.sop\platform\SecurityHonestyGovernance.sop
@ [source] C:\Project\Pinky\.sop\platform\AttentionWeightScale.sop
@ [source] C:\Project\Pinky\.sop\platform\ConceptRefinementFabric.sop
@ [source] C:\Project\Pinky\.sop\platform\ConceptAuthorityQualification.sop

& [SocialPeripheryInterestFabric] is the future network map over consented interest and periphery signals
  + [spec_status] is future_blocked_specification
  + [pattern_lineage] is public web crawler and search ranking pattern adapted to user-owned semantic interest packets
  + [operational_scope] is relationships between nodes of interest across internet sources, local SOP records, and opt-in shared social periphery packets
  + [purpose_scope] is community interest coordination, trust-lensed discovery, synchronized perspective finding, and recommendation explanation
  + [local_interest_digest] is a user-owned summary of an interest node, source relation, periphery context, evidence trace, and outside boundary
  + [shared_interest_space] is the user's reviewed set of digested interests that may be shared with a local social network under explicit policy
  + [local_social_network] is the user's selected trusted contacts, groups, communities, or lenses that may exchange interest packets
  + [interest_node] is a subject, source, idea, question, project, document, page, artifact, community topic, or SOP record that attracts attention
  + [interest_relation] is a weighted edge between interest_nodes based on correlation, causation claim, citation, co-attention, shared periphery, trust lens, or user judgement
  + [periphery_signature] is the surrounding subject set, relation hints, boundary notes, uncertainty, and caution that travel with a local_interest_digest
  + [cross_network_periphery_scan] is future opt-in comparison of shared periphery signatures across social networks
  + [synchronized_perspective] is independently shared periphery overlap across different users, communities, or lenses
  + [recommendation_candidate] is a surfaced interest_node or association route raised by overlap, trust-lens weighting, and explanation gates
  + [recommendation_explanation] is why the node surfaced, which periphery overlaps contributed, which trust lenses affected it, and what uncertainty remains
  + [concept_refinement_fabric] is the specialization where interest nodes become concept nodes whose contributed explanations can replace scoped roots through visible votes, trust lenses, and lineage preservation
  + [concept_authority_qualification] is the specialization where categorized responses and primacy votes help produce scoped qualified source material after evidence and moderation gates
  + [crawler_boundary] is scan only user-consented packets, public sources selected by policy, or local records selected by the user
  + [implementation_boundary] is no internet crawler, social graph scanner, browser extension, packet exchange, or recommendation automation until required gates exist
  + [residual_outside] is raw browsing history, private messages, credentials, hidden identity, unconsented social graph, surveillance, global truth, and central ranking monopoly

  ? [use_when: SOP Swarm Fabric needs to express social-network interest mapping, shared periphery overlap, or trust-lensed recommendations]
    = activate [SocialPeripheryInterestFabric]

  = must: treat this as the same crawler-search pattern at a different semantic and social scope
  = must: keep local_interest_digest user-owned and local by default
  = must: share only reviewed digests or packets, never raw private browsing or private social data by default
  = must: treat local_social_network as the transfer medium for community interest coordination, not as an extraction target
  = must: compare periphery_signature overlap before raising cross-network recommendations
  = must: label synchronized_perspective as correlation and social resonance, not truth, safety, or endorsement
  = must: route recommendation_candidate through trust_lens, Security, Honesty, LocalIdentityConsumption, and explanation gates
  = must: use ConceptRefinementFabric when the social fabric anchors community attention around concepts, explanation candidates, root replacement, voting, or concept lineage
  = must: use ConceptAuthorityQualification when a refined concept is being considered as citeable or authoritative source material
  = must: make every recommendation explainable by visible overlaps, sources, trust lenses, and residual outside
  = must: treat crawler_boundary as kernel-level before any automation
  = must: preserve dissenting or cautionary periphery as part of the recommendation context
  = should: support local-only use before cross-network exchange
  = should: let users maintain multiple social lenses such as friends, project group, expert circle, skeptic circle, safety lens, and topic community
  = should: decay stale periphery signatures unless reaffirmed
  - never: silently crawl a user's browser, private messages, contacts, credentials, or social graph
  - never: treat popularity, heat, overlap, or synchronized perspective as proof of truth
  - never: build centralized compulsory rankings from user interest packets
  - never: share packets beyond the user's selected social or trust scope
  - never: implement network exchange from this specification alone

& [InterestPacketShape] is the future shareable digest shape for one node of interest
  + [packet_status] is future_schema_candidate
  + [interest_node_key] is normalized subject handle or source-bound interest handle
  + [source_pointer] is URL, SOP path, document pointer, content hash, or redacted source handle
  + [digest_summary] is user-reviewed description of what attracted attention
  + [periphery_signature] is nearby subjects, relation hints, uncertainty, caution, and outside
  + [relation_vector] is correlation, citation, co-attention, contrast, support, contradiction, causation_claim, or route_hint
  + [evidence_pointer_set] is source, citation, screenshot hash, SOP path, review note, or user assertion label
  + [trust_scope] is self, friend, group, community, expert, topic, temporary, anonymous, public, or blocked
  + [privacy_scope] is local_only, selected_contacts, selected_group, federated_lens, public_digest, or withdrawn
  + [rating_vector] is usefulness, relevance, novelty, confidence, uncertainty, caution, quality, and objection
  + [explanation_note] is why the packet exists and how it should or should not influence recommendations
  + [expiry_or_decay] is when the packet loses weight unless reaffirmed
  + [outside] is raw private content, hidden identity, proof of truth, compulsory ranking, and unreviewed data

  = must: carry privacy_scope and trust_scope
  = must: distinguish evidence_pointer_set from user judgement and correlation heat
  = must: allow withdrawal, tombstone, or local-only lock

& [PeripheryOverlapRecommendation] is the recommendation pattern from shared periphery across social networks
  + [overlap_input] is two or more periphery_signature records shared under compatible privacy_scope and trust_scope
  + [overlap_signal] is shared nearby subjects, relation hints, repeated route hints, common evidence pointer patterns, or complementary caution notes
  + [network_scope] is one local social network, selected trusted group, federated community, or cross-lens comparison
  + [recommendation_trigger] is overlap depth, trust-lens weight, novelty, relevance to current focus, or repeated independent emergence
  + [recommendation_output] is interest_node suggestion, route_to_source, related community signal, cautionary warning, or ask_user_to_review
  + [explanation_required] is overlap sources, trust lens used, uncertainty, dissent, manipulation risk, and local reason for surfacing
  + [outside] is proof of truth, universal endorsement, hidden ranking, and unexplainable promotion

  = must: require explanation_required before recommendation promotion
  = must: treat weak overlap as periphery, not focus
  = must: route suspicious overlap through manipulation_risk inspection
  = should: let the user accept, ignore, downrank, or block the recommendation

& [FederatedPeripheryCrawlerBoundary] is the future crawler boundary for social periphery scanning
  + [crawler_status] is future_blocked
  + [allowed_scan_surface] is local_interest_digest, shared_interest_space, opt-in InterestPacketShape records, and selected public sources under user policy
  + [blocked_scan_surface] is raw private browsing, contacts, private messages, forms, credentials, unconsented social graph, and background telemetry
  + [scan_goal] is find compatible periphery signatures, association routes, community interest clusters, and recommendation candidates
  + [scan_output] is local index update, periphery overlap report, recommendation candidate, manipulation warning, or outside note
  + [abuse_risk] is surveillance, deanonymization, Sybil influence, brigading, targeted manipulation, popularity capture, and social pressure loops
  + [outside] is crawler automation before privacy, consent, transport, and abuse gates

  = must: require consent, visibility, pause, deletion, redaction, and export controls before any crawler automation
  = must: keep crawler output local unless user chooses a shareable packet
  = must: make abuse_risk visible in every cross-network scan report

& [ImplementationGate_SocialPeripheryInterestFabric] is the future implementation readiness boundary
  + [implementation_status] is blocked_until_gates_satisfied
  + [required_gate_set] is privacy_threat_model, consent_interface, packet_schema, redaction_engine, identity_signature_model, trust_lens_engine, recommendation_explanation_model, social_scope_policy, federated_transport_policy, manipulation_resistance_model, local_storage_model, export_delete_controls, and abuse_response_policy
  + [first_safe_prototype] is local-only synthetic packet comparison over hand-written InterestPacketShape samples
  + [blocked_work] is browser crawler, social graph import, packet federation, recommendation automation, public indexing, remote sync, and contact discovery
  + [outside] is any implementation that collects, shares, ranks, or recommends user activity without explicit local control

  = must: begin with synthetic or user-provided sample packets before any real internet or social data
  = must: prove explanation quality and privacy boundary before any recommendation automation
  = must: keep network exchange blocked until transport, identity, abuse, and deletion gates exist

(social_periphery_interest_fabric) :local_interest_digest: /privacy_scope and trust_scope/ |private_outside|
  + [local_interest_digest] is user-owned reviewed interest and periphery record
  + [periphery_signature] is surrounding context that enables overlap search
  + [shared_interest_space] is selected digest set shared under policy
  + [synchronized_perspective] is compatible overlap across social networks or lenses
  + [recommendation_candidate] is surfaced only with explanation and gates
  |private_outside| raw browsing, private messages, credentials, hidden identity, unconsented social graph, surveillance, and global truth

/ [local_interest_digest], [periphery_signature] -(Packetizes)> [InterestPacketShape], [privacy_scope], [trust_scope], [outside]
* [InterestPacketShape], [local_social_network], [trust_lens] -(Transfers)> [shared_interest_space], [community_interest_coordination], [private_outside]
* [periphery_signature], [cross_network_periphery_scan] -(Finds)> [synchronized_perspective], [recommendation_candidate], [manipulation_risk]
* [recommendation_candidate], [recommendation_explanation], [SecurityHonestyGovernance] -(PromotesOrBlocks)> [user_review], [focus_candidate], [outside]
